Farmington first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2000 U.S. census]].<ref name=2000CensusCA/>

===2020===
The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Farmington had a population of 220. The population density was {{convert|86.5|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The ethnic makeup of Farmington was 125 (56.8%) [[Non-Hispanic white]], 9 (4.1%) from two or more races (not Hispanic or Latino), and 86 (39.1%) [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]].<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Farmington CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0623630 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 20, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 89 households, out of which 30 (33.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 41 (46.1%) were married-couple households, 8 (9.0%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 24 (27.0%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 16 (18.0%) had a male householder with no partner present. 23 households (25.8%) were one person, and 9 (10.1%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.47.<ref name=DP1/> There were 61 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (68.5% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Farmington CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0623630 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=May 20, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 61 people (27.7%) under the age of 18, 16 people (7.3%) aged 18 to 24, 55 people (25.0%) aged 25 to 44, 44 people (20.0%) aged 45 to 64, and 44 people (20.0%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 38.0{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 109.5 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 90 housing units at an average density of {{convert|35.4|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 89 (98.9%) were occupied. Of these, 47 (52.8%) were owner-occupied, and 42 (47.2%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

===2010===
The [[2010 United States census]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0623630|title=2010 Census Interactive Population Search: CA - Farmington CDP|publisher=U.S. Census Bureau|access-date=July 12, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161228124605/http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=06:0623630|archive-date=December 28, 2016|url-status=dead}}</ref> reported that Farmington had a population of 207. The population density was {{convert|81.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Farmington was 164 (79.2%) [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 7 (3.4%) [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 1 (0.5%) [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 6 (2.9%) [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0 (0.0%) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 18 (8.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 11 (5.3%) from two or more races.  [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 42 persons (20.3%).

The Census reported that 207 people (100% of the population) lived in households, 0 (0%) lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0 (0%) were institutionalized.

There were 79 households, out of which 26 (32.9%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 46 (58.2%) were [[marriage|opposite-sex married couples]] living together, 5 (6.3%) had a female householder with no husband present, 6 (7.6%) had a male householder with no wife present.  There were 6 (7.6%) [[POSSLQ|unmarried opposite-sex partnerships]], and 0 (0%) [[same-sex partnerships|same-sex married couples or partnerships]]. 14 households (17.7%) were made up of individuals, and 7 (8.9%) had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.62.  There were 57 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (72.2% of all households); the average family size was 2.98.

The population was spread out, with 45 people (21.7%) under the age of 18, 13 people (6.3%) aged 18 to 24, 49 people (23.7%) aged 25 to 44, 73 people (35.3%) aged 45 to 64, and 27 people (13.0%) who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 43.9 years. For every 100 females, there were 102.9 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 102.5 males.

There were 98 housing units at an average density of {{convert|38.6|/sqmi|/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}, of which 54 (68.4%) were owner-occupied, and 25 (31.6%) were occupied by renters. The homeowner vacancy rate was 11.5%; the rental vacancy rate was 10.7%.  128 people (61.8% of the population) lived in owner-occupied housing units and 79 people (38.2%) lived in rental housing units.

